However, it is generally considered that this way of buying music (either via GSM, the Internet, or even the wireless internet) will dominate the music industry in the future.
Most people always wear their mobiles on their own.
Whenever you wanted to listen to something, you just got to get the mobile out of your pocket, while you forgot your MP3 player at home.
However, it is also important if you always have listeners or a handsfree with connection.
If this is not the case, you can use the built-in enclosures, which have almost all the mobiles, but a minimum of MP3 players.
For many, the main advantage of musical furniture is their price.
The least expensive normally cost less than three thousand.
For a price of three thousand crowns, you can already have a very suitable walkman.
In most cases, however, you will be limited by the lack of output for ordinary listeners.
The price of the best phones and the best tools, also with an entry for ordinary listeners, does not exceed fifteen thousand.
On the other hand, readers have the advantage of having an easy order.
