Freight transport (MHD) will introduce, on Wednesday, the chip into their ticketing system
Wednesday, October 1, 2008 will be recorded in the history of the Pražský Dopravní podnik (the Pragois Transportation Agency) as the date on which the first passengers will be placed in the subway, trams and buses, which, instead of having a paper ticket, will have an electronic coupon in their pocket.
At the moment, the latter is accessible for about a hundred thousand people, owners of the Opencard chip card.
Passengers can buy a coupon 30 days or 90 days (the coupon will be valid as from 1 January 2009) and at the same time have it recorded on their smart card at the information points and offices of the Dopravní podnik (the Transportation Agency), located at the metro stations Muzeum, Městek, Nádraží Holešovice, Anděl, Roztyly, Letany, Kobylisy, Rajská zahrada, Kačerov and Luka.
From yesterday on, there is also the possibility to purchase coupons via the Internet on the Dopravní podnik web pages: www.dpp.cz.
Over four hundred people benefited from the service during the morning.
Those who will start using the online store can permanently forget the windows in the metro stations, where they so far had to tread impatience in long queues in order to obtain paper tickets.
In fact, they will purchase their coupon online and will be recorded on their Opencard card in one of the thirteen Městská knihovna (municipal libraries).
"At these points of contact, there is a window at the disposal of passengers with trained staff, which will help those interested with the internet purchase and will also record the coupon they purchased on their card," said the spokesman for the Martin Opatrný project.
In addition to libraries, it will also be possible to record electronic coupons on the Opencard in automatic distributors installed in the vestibule of several metro stations.
What do these distributors look like?
They are red, remind the machines to compose tickets and passengers may have already noticed them in the metro stations Roztyly, Budějovická, I. P. Pavlova, Florenc and Vltavská.
"Today, the city has five, but by the end of the year, there should be ninety," Opatrný added.
An automatic will control the coupon instead of the driver
Autos that will work from tomorrow, are easy to use.
Simply enter the Opencard chip card and the previously purchased coupon will register itself on the card.
Electronic coupons are valid from tomorrow not only in the capital, but also around the city.
